NIH malaria cell image dataset

Source: The dataset is uploaded from Kaggle and has been sourced from the US National Library of Medicine's NIH repository,
meticulously curated by researchers at the Lister Hill National Center for Biomedical Communications.

Total Volume: The repository consists of 27,560 images of segmented cells extracted from
Giemsa-stained thin blood smear slides.

Class Distribution: The data is perfectly balanced, containing exactly 13,780 images of parasitized cells 
and 13,780 images of uninfected healthy cells.  

Algorithmic Significance: This perfect 1.0 imbalance ratio is an advantage in medical datasets 
as it prevents the deep learning model from developing a predictive bias toward a majority class.

